Andrew O'Neill (born 14 September 1979) is a British comedian, musician, presenter, and writer who lives in London.
Born in Portsmouth in 1979, O'Neill grew up in the London suburban town of Wallington.
They did their first comedy performance at the age of ten, and started their stand-up career on 16 January 2002 at the Laughing Horse, Camden.
In 2017 they published their first book, A History of Heavy Metal.
